            why. No partial load, no fallback to defaults.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="fc">
          <h3>Memory ceiling reached</h3>
          <p>
            Eviction policy fires per operator config. The daemon does
            not allocate past the ceiling; it does not resize; the OOM
            reaper does not get a chance to kill it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="fc">
          <h3>Unrecognized configuration key</h3>
          <p>
            Rejected at parse time with line + column. A typo in
            <code>bantime</code> is a startup failure, not a silent
            default-to-zero.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="fc">
          <h3>netlink ACK returns an error</h3>
          <p>
            Errors are surfaced as typed Zig errors with specific
            errnos. The operation is logged as failed; the daemon does
            not lose track of state or silently proceed as if the
            operation succeeded.
          </p>
